22:25.840 --> 22:27.680
whatever you've heard

22:27.760 --> 22:29.280
I don't need to make threats.

22:32.720 --> 22:34.240
My comrade brothers and sisters...

22:34.480 --> 22:36.480
Your brothers and sisters!
All right, listen,

22:37.320 --> 22:39.640
I will conduct myself as a businessman.

22:39.800 --> 22:40.840
Who says sweetheart.

22:40.920 --> 22:44.760
You say there's a ten shilling disparity
between male and female cutters

22:44.880 --> 22:46.440
in two of my factories.

22:46.520 --> 22:48.400
Very well.

22:48.480 --> 22:51.080
I will increase the pay
of the female cutters

22:51.160 --> 22:53.160
in this factory by five shillings

22:54.360 --> 22:56.920
and I will cut the pay
of the male cutters

22:57.080 --> 22:59.400
in the Rover by five shillings,

23:00.480 --> 23:03.160
thereby achieving
your sacred fucking parity.

23:04.680 --> 23:06.280
And I will tell the men

23:06.360 --> 23:07.760
with families to feed

23:08.560 --> 23:10.880
whose idea it was to cut their pay.

23:10.960 --> 23:14.520
You do that, I will bring
all my members out on strike.

23:14.600 --> 23:17.400
Oh, yeah?
A week after Christmas, you think so?

23:18.000 --> 23:19.400
You know, everything
you've said here today

23:19.480 --> 23:21.280
and the fact that
we're having this meeting today

23:22.080 --> 23:24.840
tells me that you're a woman
without a family.

23:26.240 --> 23:30.120
And everything I hear about you tells me
you're a man without a family as well.

23:32.040 --> 23:35.160
My comrade brothers and sisters
are not afraid of you, Mr Shelby.

23:35.800 --> 23:38.680
I will call an extraordinary meeting
of my executive committee

23:38.760 --> 23:40.360
as soon as Boxing Day.

23:40.440 --> 23:42.600
You will hear the whistles blow
all across Birmingham.

23:45.640 --> 23:48.040
I've heard
lots of whistles blow, sweetheart.

23:52.480 --> 23:54.720
(EXHALES)

24:13.240 --> 24:15.800
The post has arrived, Mr Shelby.

24:22.880 --> 24:23.880
I'm sorry to keep asking

24:23.960 --> 24:26.240
but chef needs to know
how many for dinner tomorrow.

24:27.440 --> 24:28.280
He's new,

24:28.720 --> 24:30.600
he's foreign, he gets very upset.

24:32.880 --> 24:34.080
Right. Well, you tell chef

24:34.160 --> 24:36.760
there'll be 27 guests
for Christmas dinner tomorrow.

24:36.840 --> 24:38.240
Twenty-seven?

24:38.320 --> 24:40.160
-Family?
-Yep.

24:40.240 --> 24:42.120
I thought Charlie could do
with some company

24:42.200 --> 24:45.200
so I asked Johnny Dogs
if he knew anyone who liked to eat goose

24:46.280 --> 24:48.000
and he said he knew 26.

24:50.280 --> 24:53.880
Tell chef I want ten geese,
a buck cut into steaks,

24:55.120 --> 24:56.600
some trout from the river,

24:57.920 --> 25:00.600
fetch whisky, brandy and wine
from the cellar, best we have.

25:01.680 --> 25:02.880
There will be children?

25:03.600 --> 25:04.680
Lots of children.

25:05.200 --> 25:07.880
With Johnny's tribe, new ones
might be born on the floor,

25:08.480 --> 25:11.240
so have...
have mops and buckets ready, eh?

25:12.840 --> 25:15.600
And I want you at the table, Frances,
so make it 28.

25:16.600 --> 25:17.920
I will be busy.

25:19.240 --> 25:20.520
You've put up with me this past year,

25:20.600 --> 25:22.400
looked after Charlie
when I've been on business,

25:22.480 --> 25:25.160
tomorrow you will eat at my table.

25:28.360 --> 25:30.200
Things will get better,
I think, next year.

25:34.160 --> 25:35.440
Uh-huh.

26:32.960 --> 26:36.520
Gets much warmer than here in the
summer, much colder in the winter.

26:36.600 --> 26:37.840
ARTHUR: I knew it.

26:37.920 --> 26:39.520
But parts of it
are just like Birmingham.

26:39.840 --> 26:42.680
Yeah. Shit and smoke
the same everywhere.

26:42.760 --> 26:46.200
Hmm. What about you, Linda?
You working?

26:47.560 --> 26:49.440
I've been seeking work as a teacher.

26:49.520 --> 26:51.280
-ARTHUR: Teacher.
-Hmm, but you know,

26:51.600 --> 26:54.840
it's quite difficult. The Shelby name
is always in the papers.

26:56.800 --> 26:59.040
And, uh, what do you get up to
all day, Arthur?

26:59.840 --> 27:03.240
As you know Arthur's previous endeavours
have left us with no need for a salary.

27:04.640 --> 27:06.440
Arthur occupies his time in the garden,

27:07.000 --> 27:08.560
doing voluntary work.

27:09.280 --> 27:10.920
He drives old people and cripples.

27:11.600 --> 27:15.040
-Oh.
-Yeah, well, something to do.

27:16.840 --> 27:18.080
I wanna open a garage.

27:18.960 --> 27:20.720
-Someday.
-Fixing cars, you know?

27:20.800 --> 27:22.800
Sometimes cars attract ambitious men.

27:24.240 --> 27:25.680
Yeah, but...

27:26.680 --> 27:28.720
-I like fixing cars.
-Hmm.

27:31.120 --> 27:32.560
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

27:33.480 --> 27:34.800
I'll go.

27:34.880 --> 27:36.680
I got it.

27:41.760 --> 27:43.360
Maypole 244.

27:44.400 --> 27:46.880
Arthur, have you checked your post?

27:48.320 --> 27:50.000
I just got served a black hand.

27:51.600 --> 27:53.960
I just got delivered
a black fucking hand to the house

27:55.120 --> 27:56.400
from Luca Changretta.

27:57.560 --> 27:59.080
Jesus.

28:00.480 --> 28:01.720
Jesus Christ!

28:04.840 --> 28:06.600
Wait a minute, John, which one's Luca?

28:07.400 --> 28:09.800
<i>The old man's oldest son.</i>

28:09.880 --> 28:12.520
<i>He was gonna get done
for killing a bank clerk in a robbery.</i>

28:13.040 --> 28:15.080
<i>So his old man
sent him back to New York.</i>

28:16.320 --> 28:18.640
You know what the black hand
means among the wops, Arthur?

28:19.920 --> 28:21.000
It's Mafia shit.

28:22.280 --> 28:24.040
The Sicilian fucking Mafia.

28:25.520 --> 28:27.480
<i>Just check your post, Arthur.</i>

28:35.040 --> 28:36.520
Arthur, I was just leaving.

28:36.600 --> 28:38.480
No, you're not.

28:38.560 --> 28:41.280
I need... I need to talk to you.

28:41.360 --> 28:42.840
-Arthur?
-It's all right, Linda.

28:43.480 --> 28:45.240
Stay here. Ada, please?

28:50.040 --> 28:52.960
Linda, you stay here.

29:02.480 --> 29:03.760
Did you say Mafia?

29:04.800 --> 29:07.120
Esme, I need to make a call.

29:07.200 --> 29:09.080
-No.
-I need to make a fucking call.

29:09.160 --> 29:10.840
-Give it here!
-What the fuck is this?

29:10.920 --> 29:12.960
-Give it here!
-Tell me what the fuck it is.

29:13.040 --> 29:14.520
-Give it here.
-What is it?

29:15.360 --> 29:18.240
It's from Luca Changretta,
All right? We killed his dad.

29:19.400 --> 29:20.840
I remember.

29:20.920 --> 29:21.920
It was Tommy who killed him.

29:22.000 --> 29:24.600
It was fucking...
Arthur pulled the trigger.

29:25.480 --> 29:27.560
All right, it was mercy,
but it was Arthur.

29:28.440 --> 29:30.200
Anyway, it makes no fucking difference.

29:30.760 --> 29:32.000
For the wops it's family.

29:32.920 --> 29:36.320
The black hand came here,
everybody will have got one.

29:36.400 --> 29:38.480
They're coming for us all.

29:42.880 --> 29:44.600
We made an agreement.

29:45.600 --> 29:47.400
We made a solemn promise.

29:48.800 --> 29:50.440
We're the family now.

29:51.240 --> 29:52.800
(SPEAKS ROMANI)

29:59.840 --> 30:01.680
Here, look at that.

30:02.960 --> 30:05.840
That's from Changretta's son, Luca.

30:06.640 --> 30:09.800
How the fuck he knows where I live, eh?

30:10.440 --> 30:12.840
And why has he waited a year?

30:12.960 --> 30:15.000
I'm gonna see Tommy next,
I'll talk to him.

30:16.560 --> 30:18.080
I've been served a black hand

30:18.800 --> 30:21.480
and she won't even let me keep
a fucking spud gun in the house.

30:21.560 --> 30:23.080
Go to a hotel.

30:23.160 --> 30:24.920
It's Christmas Eve, Ada.

30:28.800 --> 30:31.280
I've got a gun in the glove compartment,
you take that for now.

30:31.600 --> 30:33.120
I'll talk to Tommy and have him call,

30:33.200 --> 30:34.640
just make sure
you get to the phone first.

30:34.720 --> 30:36.160
-Yeah.
-Now,

30:36.760 --> 30:38.880
hug me like you came out here
'cause you were emotional.

30:39.560 --> 30:41.200
I am emotional.

30:41.280 --> 30:43.200
I just don't know
what fucking emotion it is.

30:44.840 --> 30:47.280
It'll be okay. I'll talk to Tommy.

30:47.680 --> 30:50.080
You talk to him.

30:55.480 --> 30:57.760
You and me both, brother.

31:04.440 --> 31:05.760
Ada?

31:07.040 --> 31:08.520
You wait there.

31:08.600 --> 31:10.760
You won't leave empty-handed,
here you go, look.

31:11.120 --> 31:13.120
Some eggs, you get them
to Polly, all right?

31:14.000 --> 31:16.640
And you, keep your eyes on the road.

31:18.080 --> 31:20.040
-Take care.
-Mm.

31:27.280 --> 31:29.080
Who was on the phone, Arthur?

31:29.160 --> 31:31.800
John, wishing me Merry Christmas.

31:36.320 --> 31:37.840
Come inside,

31:37.920 --> 31:39.720
it's getting late.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.640
(SHIP'S HORN BLOWS)

32:01.600 --> 32:03.000
Thanks.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.960
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

32:31.560 --> 32:32.960
Take off the hat.

32:40.400 --> 32:42.040
Are you with those other Italians?

32:43.120 --> 32:44.680
We're Americans,

32:45.440 --> 32:47.240
says it right there on the paper.

32:48.800 --> 32:50.520
USA.

32:53.760 --> 32:55.200
And what's the purpose of your visit?

32:57.480 --> 32:58.960
Pleasure.

33:11.480 --> 33:13.640
Mum? It's me.

33:20.560 --> 33:22.600
-Left the door open.
-To change the air.

33:23.720 --> 33:25.360
I told you I was busy today,
what do you want?

33:27.920 --> 33:30.480
Why haven't you opened your post?

33:30.560 --> 33:32.000
Tidied up.

33:33.240 --> 33:35.200
Ada's coming today.

33:35.280 --> 33:36.840
She's late.

33:37.640 --> 33:40.040
Tommy asked about you today.

33:42.000 --> 33:43.760
I hope Ada's car hasn't broken down.

33:44.720 --> 33:46.720
Shelby Company Limited
still using Bentleys?

33:47.600 --> 33:49.720
Yeah.

33:49.800 --> 33:52.080
Bentleys are no good in the cold.
You should tell him.

33:53.280 --> 33:54.360
(SIGHS) I will.

33:56.040 --> 33:57.280
Any other messages for Tommy?

33:57.360 --> 33:58.680
Yeah, fuck off.

34:01.400 --> 34:03.200
He saw that your drainpipe was broken.

34:04.560 --> 34:06.520
He's worried.

34:09.120 --> 34:11.880
Is that it?
Is that all he asked about, drainpipes?

34:12.960 --> 34:15.360
No, he said that I'm to accept
that you have a gift.

34:17.200 --> 34:20.040
That you've always had a gift.

34:20.120 --> 34:21.200
What gift?

34:22.200 --> 34:23.920
Second sight.

34:24.600 --> 34:26.320
Spirits, all that gypsy stuff.

34:26.400 --> 34:27.760
He said that I'm to believe you.

34:27.840 --> 34:30.440
You think I don't hear
his voice in yours?

34:30.520 --> 34:32.440
You don't think
I recognise his strategies?

34:34.280 --> 34:36.120
-I'm still a match for him.
-Yes,

34:37.120 --> 34:38.520
you are.

34:39.120 --> 34:40.160
And you still can be.

34:42.200 --> 34:43.920
Me and Lizzie decided

34:44.000 --> 34:46.560
that this new year
we're all to turn a page.

34:49.640 --> 34:51.240
You can't spend
another year like this, Mum.

34:51.320 --> 34:52.720
Mum.

34:58.440 --> 35:00.080
Mum.

35:01.440 --> 35:03.520
Word is like a bullet to me.

35:10.160 --> 35:12.320
See your sister in that chair sometimes.

35:16.280 --> 35:18.320
Look,

35:18.400 --> 35:20.160
me and Lizzie decided.

35:22.720 --> 35:24.520
It's time.

35:27.120 --> 35:31.200
I bought these.
One for you and Ada...

35:31.920 --> 35:33.720
One for you and me.

35:35.320 --> 35:37.040
So Tommy said, keep her off the whisky?

35:42.120 --> 35:43.240
I'll drink champagne

35:43.320 --> 35:46.200
the day my son leaves the employment
of Shelby Company Ltd.

35:47.520 --> 35:50.320
You tell him that next time
he mentions fucking drainpipes.

36:07.360 --> 36:10.320
Right, now, this is your job, Charlie.

36:11.800 --> 36:14.000
Now, give those to Santa,

36:15.000 --> 36:16.480
and Rudolf.

36:16.560 --> 36:17.760
Good boy.

36:18.280 --> 36:20.200
Leave this out for Santa,
that's whisky.

36:21.120 --> 36:24.080
Now, night-night. Merry Christmas.

36:26.560 --> 36:28.800
I'll see you tomorrow.
All right? Sleep well.

36:28.880 --> 36:30.880
Come on, Charlie.

37:23.720 --> 37:25.760
(CAR ENGINE RUNNING)

37:39.840 --> 37:41.280
(SIGHS)

37:41.360 --> 37:43.160
(KNOCK <i>AT</i> DOOR)

37:54.920 --> 37:56.200
Mr Shelby, it's your sister.

37:56.720 --> 37:58.440
I know. Send her in.

38:05.960 --> 38:09.000
I've had a card, Ada. I'm guessing
Arthur and John have had one as well.

38:09.840 --> 38:12.440
"Hello, Tommy."
"Hello, Ada, welcome home."

38:12.520 --> 38:15.200
"Thanks, it's nice
to be back." (CHUCKLES)

38:17.600 --> 38:18.440
I've spoken to Moss.

38:19.120 --> 38:21.680
Moss says that Changretta
is a soldier for the Spinetta family,

38:21.760 --> 38:23.960
which means that he'll have men
with him, professional men.

38:24.040 --> 38:27.000
They usually operate
in units of around ten.

38:27.120 --> 38:29.880
Moss is checking Cunard records
to see if they're already in England.

38:30.520 --> 38:32.400
This one's for you.

38:33.440 --> 38:34.880
What is it, a time machine?

38:35.640 --> 38:38.520
My God, Tommy Shelby, is that regret?

38:39.240 --> 38:40.920
I'll open it tomorrow.

38:41.640 --> 38:45.960
So, boss, in light of the changed
circumstances, what are your orders?

38:50.120 --> 38:51.760
Changretta knows where we all live.

38:53.040 --> 38:55.840
If we stay out in the open, isolated,
he'll pick us off one by one.

38:57.040 --> 38:59.480
We need to be together in a place
even they won't dare to come.

39:01.520 --> 39:02.760
You mean, back home?

39:04.040 --> 39:05.680
Within a four-mile radius
of the Garrison,

39:05.760 --> 39:07.760
every man is a guard
and a soldier for us.

39:07.840 --> 39:09.480
I'm calling a family meeting.

39:09.560 --> 39:11.200
Charlie Strong's yard, Boxing Day.

39:12.040 --> 39:13.440
Finn's already there.

39:13.520 --> 39:15.720
You tell Polly and Michael,
I'll deal with John and Arthur.

39:15.800 --> 39:17.200
And Esme and Linda?

39:19.720 --> 39:21.640
Anyone who wants to live
to see another Christmas

39:21.720 --> 39:24.760
needs to come where it's safe.
These bastards will kill kids as well.

39:24.960 --> 39:27.320
When this business is finished we can...

39:27.400 --> 39:29.120
go our separate ways.

39:31.480 --> 39:34.160
Go and see Polly and explain.
She'll have had a card as well.

39:36.480 --> 39:38.240
Do you think I'm on the list?

39:39.760 --> 39:41.760
We're all on the list, Ada.

39:43.680 --> 39:45.080
I gave my gun to Arthur.

40:03.400 --> 40:04.600
Welcome home.

40:05.280 --> 40:06.560
Hm.

40:23.520 --> 40:25.320
Holy shit.

40:25.400 --> 40:28.240
-It's Father Christmas.
-Yeah.

40:28.320 --> 40:30.440
And if you're good

40:30.520 --> 40:32.480
you get what you deserve.

40:32.560 --> 40:34.200
Fucking come here, you.

40:52.440 --> 40:54.200
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

40:59.120 --> 41:00.920
(RINGING CONTINUES)

41:08.400 --> 41:10.080
Fuck.

41:17.720 --> 41:19.960
Yeah, put me through to Maypole 245.

41:20.520 --> 41:22.000
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

41:30.520 --> 41:32.480
-Hello?
<i>.Arthur, it's Tommy.</i>

41:33.320 --> 41:34.680
Be quick, they're asleep.

41:35.560 --> 41:38.680
Family meeting, Charlie's Yard,
Boxing Day, midday.

41:39.440 --> 41:42.400
I can't raise John
but I'll send Michael to get him.

41:43.200 --> 41:45.640
If you have to pull a gun
on Linda, do it.

41:45.720 --> 41:47.520
Merry Christmas.

41:52.440 --> 41:54.440
Merry Christmas, Tom.

42:03.760 --> 42:05.120
What did you do with them?

42:07.120 --> 42:09.560
My tablets were in the bathroom cabinet.
What did you do with them?

42:11.040 --> 42:13.040
I threw them in the lavatory.

42:14.360 --> 42:17.080
-Tommy's orders?
-No. My own decision.

42:22.520 --> 42:25.440
How am I gonna get through Christmas
without them? They close everything.

42:26.000 --> 42:27.600
How am I gonna get through Christmas
without them?

42:27.680 --> 42:29.760
-I'll help you.
-They don't open anything.

42:29.840 --> 42:31.240
Fucking no apocethary, nothing.

42:32.560 --> 42:34.680
You can move in with me
and I'll help you.

42:36.000 --> 42:38.120
How am I gonna get through
fucking Christmas,

42:38.200 --> 42:40.080
without... without anything?

42:40.680 --> 42:43.720
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

42:45.520 --> 42:47.400
You can move in with me
and I'll help you.

42:47.480 --> 42:51.840
Fuck off. Fuck off.
Fuck off, Thomas Shelby. Fuck off.

42:51.920 --> 42:54.120
It's all right, it was me.
I just want you to stop, just stop.

42:54.200 --> 42:56.040
-I just want the tablets.
-This has got to stop!

42:56.120 --> 42:58.600
Tommy said to believe in spirits
with you but I can't.

42:58.680 --> 43:00.840
Hello, Polly. Hello, Michael.

43:02.040 --> 43:03.360
Merry Christmas.

43:04.000 --> 43:05.400
Door was wide open.

43:06.040 --> 43:08.360
Fuck.

43:08.440 --> 43:11.520
I spent the whole day tidying up,
I wanted it to be nice.

43:12.120 --> 43:13.560
I wanted it to look nice.

43:13.640 --> 43:15.880
All right, Poll, it's only me.

43:15.960 --> 43:18.280
It's okay. It's okay, we can sit.

43:18.560 --> 43:22.440
Sit and talk, we'll put things
back together. It's okay.

43:23.680 --> 43:25.880
-I'll leave you two to it.
-No, you stay.

43:28.160 --> 43:30.600
Now listen, something's happened.

43:30.680 --> 43:32.400
Things have changed.

43:33.000 --> 43:35.480
Today, everyone in the family

43:36.320 --> 43:38.320
received one of these.

43:48.960 --> 43:51.800
-What does it mean?
-Tommy's called a family meeting.

43:52.760 --> 43:54.560
He wants you both to come.

44:02.120 --> 44:03.840
(KNOCK <i>AT</i> DOOR)

44:05.200 --> 44:07.000
Come.

44:13.640 --> 44:16.200
I'm really sorry
to bother you again, sir,

44:16.280 --> 44:18.800
but chef insists on knowing
what time the guests will arrive.

44:20.920 --> 44:22.800
Frances, for the last time,

44:23.800 --> 44:25.480
it's Johnny Dogs,

44:25.560 --> 44:26.800
they're gypsies,

44:26.880 --> 44:28.240
they're camped down by the river.

44:28.320 --> 44:30.720
When they're ready they'll walk up.
All right?

44:31.800 --> 44:34.320
-He says it's about preparation, sir.
-What is?

44:34.400 --> 44:36.720
He's asked specifically,

44:36.800 --> 44:39.120
will they arrive
before the King's speech or after?

44:44.400 --> 44:46.400
You said he was new, this chef.

44:48.400 --> 44:50.800
-When did he join us?
-October.

44:55.280 --> 44:57.080
October.

44:58.440 --> 44:59.920
And he's foreign?

45:00.000 --> 45:01.480
-He's Italian, sir.
-Oh.

45:04.480 --> 45:06.760
He's the best chef
we've ever had in the house.

45:07.640 --> 45:09.960
No shouting or swearing or blaspheming.

45:10.360 --> 45:12.400
-Do we know his references?
-Yes.

45:15.680 --> 45:17.720
The only problem has been his assistant.

45:18.320 --> 45:19.280
What assistant?

45:19.360 --> 45:22.600
He brought an assistant with him,
he calls him his sous chef.

45:27.440 --> 45:29.280
Are they still working, Frances?

45:29.440 --> 45:31.040
They'll be there till midnight, sir.

45:36.720 --> 45:38.640
All right, thank you.
Goodnight, you can go to bed.

45:40.200 --> 45:41.440
Merry Christmas, sir.

45:43.800 --> 45:45.120
And I thought about your offer,

45:47.320 --> 45:49.120
I'd be happy to sit at your table.

45:51.080 --> 45:52.720
All right, thank you.

46:22.080 --> 46:23.880
Mr Shelby.

46:31.760 --> 46:32.960
What's your name?

46:33.040 --> 46:34.720
-Max, Mr Shelby.
-Max.

46:38.200 --> 46:40.080
It's all right, don't get up.

46:40.160 --> 46:43.200
Oh. Sorry, sorry, sir.

46:46.760 --> 46:48.800
You knew I'm Mr Shelby?

46:48.880 --> 46:50.160
Hello, sir.

46:51.400 --> 46:53.960
I haven't taken time
to introduce myself.

46:54.960 --> 46:56.200
Antonio.

47:00.080 --> 47:02.080
What have you done that's so wrong, eh?

47:03.520 --> 47:04.840
Excuse me?

47:04.920 --> 47:07.480
Sous chef, peeling potatoes?

47:09.920 --> 47:12.080
It's an emergency, late notice.

47:12.840 --> 47:15.480
Oh, late notice.

47:16.600 --> 47:17.760
All right.

47:18.680 --> 47:20.680
All right, carry on.

47:28.560 --> 47:29.560
Antonio...

47:31.240 --> 47:33.040
Here, £10.

47:34.800 --> 47:36.520
For the late notice.

47:47.200 --> 47:49.280
(CHOPPING)

48:14.840 --> 48:16.440
You wanted to know
if my guests would arrive

48:16.520 --> 48:18.800
before or after the King's speech.

48:22.360 --> 48:24.240
-Eh?
-Yeah.

48:26.600 --> 48:28.600
It'll be after.

48:37.200 --> 48:39.120
How are you?

48:39.200 --> 48:41.760
Just... worried about tomorrow.

48:44.200 --> 48:45.800
Yeah, I'm worried about Antonio.

48:51.680 --> 48:54.960
He's been here two months
and we've not met before, it's my fault.

48:55.720 --> 48:56.880
I've been busy.

48:58.520 --> 49:00.200
Thomas Shelby.

49:03.120 --> 49:05.480
-My hand has blood.
-Oh, mine too.

49:08.880 --> 49:12.680
Hey, how much do you pay Antonio?

49:15.400 --> 49:17.120
I forget.

49:17.200 --> 49:19.160
Must be a lot.

49:19.240 --> 49:20.800
I just gave him £10,

49:21.760 --> 49:23.320
didn't mean a fucking thing to him.

49:27.760 --> 49:30.200
Maybe it isn't you that pays him.

49:42.520 --> 49:43.840
I've been reading up on you.

49:44.160 --> 49:46.440
Bertorelli, Claridge's.

49:47.440 --> 49:50.560
You used to work in a place
called San Marco's...

49:52.000 --> 49:53.440
on...

49:54.400 --> 49:55.440
on Fleet Street.

49:58.520 --> 50:00.480
I used to know the man
that owns San Marco's.

50:01.920 --> 50:03.160
A man called Darby Sabini?

50:05.360 --> 50:07.080
-I've never met him.
-No.

50:08.520 --> 50:10.680
Maybe your, um, assistant...

50:11.600 --> 50:13.600
Antonio, maybe he's met him.

50:16.120 --> 50:18.080
-Here's how it is.
-(GRUNTS)

50:18.160 --> 50:20.800
-Antonio was sent from New York?
-I don't know, please.

50:20.920 --> 50:22.640
Darby Sabini facilitated.

50:22.720 --> 50:25.200
He passed him onto you,
told you to bring him into my house,

50:25.280 --> 50:27.360
threatened to kill you
if you didn't do it.

50:29.000 --> 50:31.080
Do you want me to dress you
like you dressed that fucking stag?

50:31.200 --> 50:32.720
Please, don't...

50:35.640 --> 50:37.160
-You know about me?
-Mmm-mmm.

50:37.600 --> 50:39.440
All right.

50:39.520 --> 50:41.400
-You know what I do?
-Mmm.

50:43.440 --> 50:44.800
You wanted to know
when my guests would arrive

50:44.880 --> 50:46.600
'cause Antonio needed me alone.

50:47.200 --> 50:50.240
He's an assassin,
the plan is to kill me tomorrow.

50:52.840 --> 50:54.800
I don't know.

50:55.520 --> 50:57.480
They just said bring him here.

51:02.600 --> 51:04.400
Well, bring him here.

51:08.920 --> 51:10.160
Antonio...

51:11.840 --> 51:14.480
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

51:44.280 --> 51:46.760
Oh. (SPEAKING ITALIAN)

51:48.920 --> 51:50.200
Huh?

51:50.280 --> 51:52.240
(SCREAMS)

52:05.760 --> 52:07.560
You're a black hand!

52:08.520 --> 52:10.280
You're a black hand!

52:10.400 --> 52:14.200
How many came from New York?
Eh? How many fucking came from New York?

52:14.280 --> 52:15.440
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

52:17.520 --> 52:20.920
What did he say? Is that a curse
or a number, what did he fucking say?

52:21.360 --> 52:22.600
What did he fucking say?

52:22.680 --> 52:24.600
-He said fuck you.
-Yeah?

52:36.440 --> 52:39.000
Black hand means kill or be killed.

52:40.720 --> 52:42.720
You go back to London,

52:42.800 --> 52:44.680
you tell Darby Sabini

52:44.760 --> 52:46.600
he picked the wrong side in this war.

52:48.280 --> 52:50.920
Once we've dealt with the Americans
we're coming for him.

52:51.680 --> 52:53.160
Go on, go.

52:53.960 --> 52:55.200
Go. Oi!

52:55.920 --> 52:58.840
You tell anyone else,
I'll come and find you.

53:18.480 --> 53:19.920
TOMMY: <i>Arrow 335.</i>

53:21.280 --> 53:22.600
The Hare and the Hounds pub.

53:29.080 --> 53:31.400
Robert, yes, it's Mr Shelby.

53:33.240 --> 53:34.600
Merry Christmas to you too.

53:35.640 --> 53:38.880
Robert, is there a gypsy in the public
bar playing the fiddle for shillings?

53:39.800 --> 53:41.480
Yes,

53:41.560 --> 53:43.160
can you, uh,

53:43.240 --> 53:46.160
can you tell him I need to speak
to him? Thank you.

53:58.920 --> 54:00.320
Oh, fuck, Tom.

54:01.280 --> 54:03.040
I thought your sporting days were over.

54:03.200 --> 54:06.240
Yeah, so did I,
they keep coming back at us.

54:08.160 --> 54:11.480
There's a black stallion in the stables,
he's invisible at night. Use him.

54:12.480 --> 54:14.560
Take the body across the river
to the rough ground.

54:15.920 --> 54:18.920
-Burn him?
-No. This one's a message.

54:20.280 --> 54:21.800
Will there still be geese for dinner?

54:22.400 --> 54:25.480
-Only if you can steal 'em on the way.
-On the way where?

54:26.760 --> 54:28.480
We're going back, Johnny.

54:30.920 --> 54:32.520
Back to Small Heath.

54:32.600 --> 54:33.960
Back where you belong.

54:35.160 --> 54:37.840
(SPEAKS ROMANI)

54:38.000 --> 54:40.400
Merry Christmas,
you can keep the stallion.

54:40.920 --> 54:42.720
Christ the fucking night.

54:57.880 --> 55:01.960
Michael, they're coming today.
No, Michael, shut up and listen.

55:02.560 --> 55:06.040
Gotta get everyone out,
get Polly and Ada to Charlie's Yard.

55:06.120 --> 55:07.800
I've told Arthur but I can't reach John.

55:07.920 --> 55:11.200
When you've dropped Polly and Ada,
go to John's place and get him out.

55:11.280 --> 55:12.840
All right?

55:14.800 --> 55:17.680
-Is it Christmas?
-Not just yet. But let's go, eh?

55:18.560 --> 55:20.360
Mummy.

55:29.240 --> 55:32.120
Come on! Move.

55:46.400 --> 55:48.160
Hello?

55:51.360 --> 55:52.680
(GUN COCKING)

55:54.640 --> 55:56.640
Oh, fuck, it's you.

55:56.720 --> 55:58.680
Got nothing better to do
on Christmas morning?

55:58.760 --> 56:01.120
Tommy wants everybody
at Charlie's Yard now, come on.

56:02.360 --> 56:03.560
Get in! Get in!

56:03.760 --> 56:05.760
What's gonna happen, mate,
it's fucking Christmas.

56:06.280 --> 56:08.480
Look, John, we don't have time for this.

56:08.560 --> 56:11.200
-All right? Just come to the meeting.
-Just come in the house, have some food.

56:13.000 --> 56:14.360
-Hey.
-Tell Tommy Shelby

56:14.440 --> 56:15.400
we can look after ourselves.

56:15.480 --> 56:16.920
Tommy says that
they could come for us today.

56:17.000 --> 56:19.000
Tommy says, Tommy says.
Are you his fucking parrot?

56:19.080 --> 56:20.480
Look, it's the Mafia, all right?

56:21.080 --> 56:23.160
This is the New York Mafia
we're talking about.

56:23.240 --> 56:25.120
And we're the Peaky fucking Blinders.

56:25.200 --> 56:26.160
No, we're not, John.

56:26.920 --> 56:29.320
We're not the Peaky fucking Blinders
unless we're together.

56:30.080 --> 56:31.640
We were together in the gallows

56:31.840 --> 56:33.280
with one man missing.

56:34.600 --> 56:36.120
John.

56:36.200 --> 56:38.720
John, come to the meeting.
All right? Think about the kids.

56:39.400 --> 56:41.720
Come to the meeting
and if you want to leave, then fine.

56:42.600 --> 56:44.480
No. It's Christmas day,

56:45.160 --> 56:47.080
we're the family now,
we're staying at home.

56:50.520 --> 56:52.000
-Get in the fucking house!
-Esme.

56:54.440 --> 56:55.440
John!

57:18.000 --> 57:19.960
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

57:19.984 --> 57:24.984
http://hiqve.com/
